# ByteLib

```scalascript
case class ByteSlice(start: Int, len: Int)

// Integer division on Int fields/params must truncate on the JS lane even when
// this function is emitted across an import boundary (childGen), not just when
// it lives in the entry module. Guards v1-js-imported-int-division-loses-type.
def rawGet(bytes: ByteSlice, index: Int): Int =
  val absolute = bytes.start + index
  absolute / 64
```
